{"id":555908578,"lang":"cpp","time":"5 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1631797593,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"75 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/555908578/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"39.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    unordered_set<int>st;\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        if(!root) return false;\n        if(findTarget(root->left,k)) return true;\n        if(st.count(k-root->val)) return true;        \n        st.insert(root->val);\n        return findTarget(root->right,k);\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
